Katsina State chief judge, Justice Musa Abubakar, has constituted the state Local Government Election Petitions and Appeal Tribunal to hear petitions and appeals arising from last Monday’s local government elections in the state. The tribunal has 90 days to determine the petitions filed before it while the appeal tribunal has one month to determine the appeals arising from the decision of the tribunal. The chairmen and members of the tribunal will be inaugurated on Wednesday at the High Court of Justice Conference Hall, Katsina by 11:00 a.m. The supervising judge for the exercise, Justice Abas Abdullahi, disclosed this at a press conference in Katsina yesterday. He said, “Following the conduct of election into local government councils in Katsina State on the 11th day of April 2022 and under the powers conferred on the honourable chief judge of Katsina State by the provisions of relevant sections of local government council electoral law 2002. “The chief judge has established Local Government Election Petition and Appeals Tribunals in Katsina State. ‘’The election tribunals for Katsina and Funtua Senatorial Zones will sit in Katsina while the local government election tribunal for Daura shall sit at Daura. “Practice direction issued by the chief judge under the relevant laws to guide the filing and the conduct of the election petition and appeals is available at the secretariat of the election tribunal.’’ Concerning all processes in respect of petitions, the CJ disclosed that they were to be filed at the secretariat of Local Government Election Tribunals for ease of logistics.